OK, follow up on my previous halfbatch question. I picked up the midwest supplies groupon today, and the kit comes with an ingredients kit. I'm sticking with my plan to do a half batch, so targeting 2.5 gallons. I'll be working with a 20 qt stockpot. Should I do my boil with 2.5 gallons of water for the whole process, or should I boil 1 or 1.5 gallons and then add the rest of the water post-boil? The 20 qt pot should be plenty big to handle the full amount of water, but the kit instructions seem to assume that you're boiling 2.5 gallons of water for 5 gallons at the end, so they expect you to add quite a bit of water post boil.I'm watching some micro-batch videos on you tube, and the best one I've found has the guy doing his steeping with 0.5 gallon, then adding the rest of the water before adding the DME. He doesn't really explain why he steeped with less than the full amount of water though.
