Posted: Thu Apr 05, 2012 7:21 pm
The idea behind steeping in less than the full boil volume is that lower pH during the steep is desirable, as it prevents the leaching of tannic acids from the husk into the steeping water. The higher the grain to water ratio, the lower the pH should get, approaching 5.2, IIRC. DePending on the amount of steeping grains, you should adjust your amount of steeping water. This is also related to the temp of the steep, with higher temps also promoting tannin extraction. The thicker and darker the steep, the higher you can go.
dak
