I brewed my first 5-gallon batch last night and it was not a complete disaster. The water from my faucet is lousy, so I opted to buy a couple of 2.5-gal Poland spring jugs. I used one for the boil and the other to top-up for fermentation (which served to both decrease the time to boil on my stove and served to chill it from boiling to under 140*F). chilling it the rest of the way without a wort chiller or an ice bath was a pain - I ended up filling my tub, draining it, and filling it again. that got the wort down to 85* and I called it good. I only had one almost-boilover, when I stepped away from the pot after turning up the heat - it went from 160* to boiling a lot faster than I expected! now I'm getting decent activity out of the airlock. . . I definitely wish I had a carboy or better bottle to observe it!I'm definitely going to give serious consideration to a wort chiller before I do my next batch.
