dak wrote:How many feet of copper tubing do you need to be effective? Would 10' be too short to get proper heat transfer? 10' sections of 3/8" copper are not too expensive.You don't want sectional copper pipe...you want soft copper tube. A 5 gallon boiler should probably use a 20-25' coil. 15 gallons is probably best with at least 35', and more likely 50'.It doesn't really change anything to have a shorter coiler, it's just not as efficient at removing heat due to less dwell time. Ergo, it takes longer to cool. (then again, I suppose you could chill the water in advance too, to increase delta and thus transfer rate)
dak
