I'm thinking about my old chiller here, and assuming that coffee can was 12" across, you'd only get three wraps with a 10' coil. That doesn't seem like a lot.In any event, the water will flow at whatever rate you fill the pipe, and more cold water is always better than longer dwell time. (too much dwell time and you're really not transferring much more heat into the cooling liquid). I think, even with a 10' coil, if you bought some extra rubber tubing and ran your water feed through an ice bath (say, in the sink) it would probably work fine.
