Posted: Wed Apr 18, 2012 5:56 am
1/4" will work. It's a bit resistant to flow and has a higher surface:volume ratio than the more common 3/8". To balance this, I actually suggest going with 20' or a little less to help keep the resistance to flow low.It won't chill as fast as 3/8" at full bore, but it will still chill in ~30min with reasonably cold water. I sometimes use a submersible pump in a cooler of ice-water to chill super fast.
dak
